    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>S.A. Day Sales Ledger D, 1900-1903, records the debts and payments of individual customers. Entries refer to prescription references and purchases of various types of medication such as chloroform, cough medicine, pills, and hair tonic. Entries also include the purchases of general merchandise such as cigars, sodas, and soap.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
